Short-term: Users can quickly raise a support ticket using a simple natural language prompt, e.g., “My workspace is not functioning, can you raise a support ticket?”
Long-term: Users can automate recurring tasks such as timesheet entry by providing prompts like “Fill my W2W times by distributing 25% effort across all tasks”, and save these workflows as reusable agents in the marketplace




✅ FR 3.0 – Example Workflows (Prompt-Driven Execution & Reusable Agents)
The system shall allow users to execute workflows using natural language prompts for both short-term and long-term tasks.
The system shall support quick, one-time task execution (e.g., raising support tickets, retrieving data) with minimal user input.
The system shall interpret user intent and automatically generate or map to appropriate workflow steps.
The system shall enable users to convert executed workflows into reusable agents for future use.
The system shall support parameterization of workflows (e.g., effort distribution, date ranges, inputs).
The system shall allow users to save, edit, version, and manage reusable workflows.
The system shall enable publishing and discovery of reusable workflows in the internal marketplace.
The system shall provide real-time execution status, logs, and results to users.
The system shall support human-in-the-loop validation for critical or sensitive workflow steps.
The system shall leverage browser context and enterprise data to enhance workflow execution.
🚀 NFR 64 – Example Workflows (Performance, Reliability & Governance)
Workflow execution shall initiate within acceptable response time (e.g., <2 seconds for trigger).
The system shall support concurrent execution of workflows across multiple users and sessions at enterprise scale.
The system shall ensure reliable execution with fault tolerance, retries, and state persistence.
All workflows shall comply with enterprise security policies, including data masking and access control.
The system shall provide audit logs, execution traces, and monitoring for all workflow activities.
The system shall ensure high usability with intuitive prompt-based interaction and minimal user effort.
The system shall support versioning and backward compatibility of workflows and reusable agents.
The system shall be extensible to support new workflow types, integrations, and agent capabilities.
